<template><section class="page-hero compact"><p class="eyebrow">About Sova</p><h1>A separate language built with NovaDev.</h1><p>Sova uses NovaDev as an implementation host and shared-library provider, but owns its grammar, AST, semantic rules, runtime behavior, tooling, versioning, and release lifecycle.</p></section><section class="section content-prose"><h2>Design references</h2><p>Python informs readability and productive dynamic behavior. C++ informs language completeness and the path toward compiled tooling. Rust informs safe defaults and explicit capabilities. JavaScript, Kotlin, and Swift inform concise collections, null handling, and expressive syntax.</p><h2>Honest boundaries</h2><p>Sova 0.1v is interpreted, automatically managed, and not C++-speed. It has no manual pointers and does not provide Rust's borrow-checker guarantees.</p></section></template>
